desc: The number of academic careers a student is registered for within a term.
A code representing a student's academic load based on units taken for the term and definition of full-time (12 units for undergrad in a full term).
A code representing the student's academic level, based on number of credits completed toward a degree, at the beginning of the term.
A code representing the academic level of a student's progression toward a degree at the end of a term.
The number of academic majors a student has declared within a term.
The number of academic minors a student has declared within a term.
The number of academic programs a student is admitted to within a term.
A code indicating whether a student self-identified as being a veteran during the admission process.
The total number of students enrolled in a class.
A code indicating whether a class section in a combined class is the home or away section. This field will always contain the value HOME if the class section is not part of a combined section.
A code indicating whether the class section is considered an honors class.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Fridays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Mondays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Saturdays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Sundays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Thursdays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Tuesdays.
A code indicating whether a class is scheduled to meet on Wednesdays.
The total number of students enrolled in the class. For combined sections, it is the total number of students enrolled in all combined sections (home and non-home) of the class.
A code indicating whether the basis for combining sections of a class is cross listed.
A code indicating whether the basis for combining sections of a class is meet together.
A code indicating whether the basis for combining sections of a class is undergraduate graduate.
A code representing the level of a student's primary career.

A code representing the type of course section. Courses can have more than one component. At course level, all the possible components of a course are identified, and are designated as optional or non-optional.

The official grade that appears on a student's transcript which can be the translated value of Course Grade Input Code as defined by school/college grading policy or in the case of transfer credit the articulated grade to distinguish the type of credit earned.
A number which identifies each offering of a course. A course may have multiple offerings if the same course is offered by more than one department i.e: cross listing.
A code indicating if a student's grade in the class or credits for a transferred course, count toward accumulated credit.
A code indicating whether a facility has the 16mm Film (Movies) Projection room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the 35mm Film (Movies) Projection room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Auditorium Seating room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Tables (Any) Seating room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Blackout (Room Darkening) room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Chalkboard Over 25 Foot Board room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Digital Data&Video Projection room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Document Camera Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the DVD Player Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Lecture Capture Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Mac (Macintosh) Computer Classroom room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Moveable Tablet Chair Seating room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Tables Moveable Seating room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the PC (Personal Computer) Computer Classroom room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Computer Podium Mac (Macintosh) Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Computer Podium PC (Personal Computer) Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Program Sound Amplification room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Voice Sound Amplification room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Stage Layout room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Table Conf/Seminar Seating room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Tiered Floor Layout room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the VCR Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Video Conferencing Equipment room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a facility has the Whiteboard Over 25 Foot Board room characteristic.
A code indicating whether a student is enrolled in any honors program during the term.
A code indicating whether or not the student has completed high school calculus.
A code indicating whether or not the student has completed a high school chemistry class with a laboratory.
A number respresenting the grade point average a student earned in high school.
A code indicating if the grade is included in the system calculated Grade Point Average.
A code representing the instruction delivery method for a course.
A code indicating whether the class has multiple meeting patterns.
A number representing the student's cumulative grade point average at the end of the previous term. Note: The field will be null if the student's career level changes or there is no previous term.
A code representing a student's primary career based on enrollment hours.
A code indicating the registration status of a student.
A code representing a student's residency for fee assessment purposes as defined by University policy.
A code indicating whether a student is a member of the Residential College Michigan Learning Community.
A code representing an aggregate of courses by instructional area, under which a particular course is offered at U of M.
A code representing a class scheduling/enrollment time period within a term.
A code indicating whether a student was raised by a single parent. Note: This data is self- reported on the student's admission application.
A code indicating whether a student is enrolled in any supplemental study plans.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having Asian ethnicity.
The self-reported birth month of a student.
The self-reported birth year of a student.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having Black ethnicity.
A code representing a student's status relative to United States citizenship. A blank value in this field indicates that the data was not available in HEPROD.
A code representing a student's single race/ethnicity reporting category as defined by the federal government's reporting requirements.
A code representing the gender of a student.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having Hispanic ethnicity.

A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as Hispanic or Latino using the federal data collection standards. Students who have self-identified as Hispanic or Latino will be categorized as such even if they identify other races or ethnicities within which they belong.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having Hawaiian ethnicity.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as more than one race/ethnicity.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having Native American ethnicity.
A code indicating whether a student has learned and used English from early childhood.

A code indicating whether a student is considered an underrepresented minority as defined institutionally. The code is set to 'Y' when the student has an ethnicity detail code of AMIND, BLACK, PACIF, or HISPA.
A code indicating whether a student has self-identified as having White ethnicity.
A code indicating whether a student is enrolled in any teaching certificate plans.
The number of graduate academic degrees a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of majors within a graduate degree(s) a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of minors within a graduate degree(s) a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of other (e.g. Teaching Certificates) academic degrees a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of undergraduate academic degrees a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of majors within an undergraduate degree(s) a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
The number of minors within an undergraduate degree(s) a student has earned at the University of Michigan.
A number representing the number of credit hours taken that count toward grade point average for the term. This includes UNT_INPROG_GPA and UNT_PASSD_GPA.
A number representing the number of credit hours taken that do not count toward grade point average for the term. This includes UNT_INPROG_NOGPA and UNT_PASSD_NOGPA.
A number representing the total credit hours earned by a student in a particular course which are applicable toward a degree or certificate within a given program.

A number reflecting the specific credit hours elected by a student for each unique section within a course. This is also the number of units included in the Grade Point Average calculation when the course is included in the Grade Point Average.
